headline: Stock Index Futures Slip as Trump Picks Warsh for Fed Chair
summary: March S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESH26) are down -0.40%, and March Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQH26) are down -0.47% this morning after U.S. President Donald Trump nominated Kevin Warsh as the next Federal Reserve chair.

headline: Is United Rentals (URI) Attractive After Recent Share Price Pullback?
summary: If you are wondering whether United Rentals' current share price still reflects good value, you are not alone. This article focuses squarely on what that price might mean for investors today. The stock recently closed at US$787.04, with a 17.7% decline over the past 7 days, a 3.7% decline over 30 days, and returns of 2.6% over 1 year, 78.1% over 3 years, and 212.8% over 5 years. headline: United Rentals Q4 Earnings Call Highlights
summary: United Rentals (NYSE:URI) used its latest investor conference call to review record 2025 results, discuss demand trends across its general rental and specialty businesses, and outline 2026 guidance that management said points to another year of profitable growth.
